President Trump held a press conference at Joint Base Andrews, Maryland, where he made several remarks on various topics. He announced that he has commuted the sentence of Rod Blagojevich, who served eight years in jail. Trump also expressed his confidence in Attorney General William Barr and defended his use of social media. He stated that he has not given any thought to pardoning Roger Stone, Paul Manafort, or Michael Flynn. Trump discussed his concerns about national security and his desire for U.S. companies to be able to sell technology to other countries. He also addressed issues related to Afghanistan, Venezuela, Turkey, and China. Trump mentioned his upcoming campaign schedule and his plans to visit Nevada and California. He expressed his belief that President Xi of China is handling the coronavirus situation professionally and praised his efforts. Trump also mentioned that a search is underway to identify the anonymous author of a book critical of his administration.